{"title_page": "Sussana Dantjie", "text_new": "{{short description|Speaker of the North West Provincial Legislature}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| honorific-prefix    = [[The Honourable]]\n| name                = Sussana Dantjie\n| native_name         = \n| native_name_lang    = \n| honorific-suffix    = [[Member of the Provincial Legislature|MPL]]\n| image               = \n| image_size          = \n| smallimage          = <!--If this is specified, \"image\" should not be.-->\n| alt                 = \n| caption             =\n| office              = Speaker of the [[North West Provincial Legislature]]\n| deputy              = [[Viola Motsumi]] (2019\u2013present)<br/>[[Jane Manganye]] (2014\u201319)\n| term_start          = 21 May 2014\n| term_end            = \n| predecessor         = [[Supra Mahumapelo]]\n| successor           = \n| office1             = Member of the [[North West Provincial Legislature]]\n| term_start1         = 21 May 2014\n| term_end1           = \n| predecessor1        = \n| successor1          = \n| office2             = Member of the [[National Assembly of South Africa]]\n| term_start2         = 6 May 2009\n| term_end2           = 6 May 2014\n| predecessor2        = \n| successor2          = \n| birthname           = Sussana Rebecca Tsebe\n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1971|08|02|df=y}}\n| birth_place         = \n| death_date          =  \n| death_place         = \n| citizenship         =\n| nationality         = [[South Africa]]n\n| party               = [[African National Congress]]\n| otherparty          = \n| spouse              = Lungile Dantjie<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://mg.co.za/article/2018-03-02-00-north-wests-economy-inspires-confidence/ |title = North West's economy inspires confidence|date = 2 March 2018}}</ref>\n| partner             =  <!--For those with a domestic partner and not married-->\n| relations           = \n| children            = \n| residence           = \n| education           = \n| alma_mater          = \n| occupation          = \n| profession          = Politician\n| known_for           = \n| committees          = \n| portfolio           = \n| awards              =  \n| website             = \n}}\n'''Sussana Rebecca Dantjie''' (n\u00e9e '''Tsebe'''; born 2 August 1971) is a South African politician who serves as the Speaker of the [[North West Provincial Legislature]]. Elected in 2014, she was re-elected in 2019. She took office as an MPL in May 2014. She was previously a Member of the [[National Assembly of South Africa]] from 2009 to 2014. Dantjie is a member of the [[African National Congress]] (ANC).<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.sanews.gov.za/south-africa/supra-mahumapelo-elected-premier-nw |title = Supra Mahumapelo elected premier of NW|date = 21 May 2014}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.iol.co.za/news/south-africa/north-west/anc-appoints-presiding-officers-in-north-west-23685307 | title=ANC appoints presiding officers in North West}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n==External links==\n*[https://www.pa.org.za/person/sussana-rebecca-dantjie/ Sussana Rebecca Dantjie \u2013 People's Assembly]\n{{SouthAfrica-politician-stub}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Dantjie, Sussana}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1971 births]]\n[[Category:Tswana people]]\n[[Category:Members of the North West Provincial Legislature]]\n[[Category:Women members of provincial legislatures of South Africa]]\n[[Category:Women legislative speakers]]\n[[Category:South African women in politics]]\n[[Category:African National Congress politicians]]\n[[Category:People from North West (South African province)]]\n[[Category:Members of the National Assembly of South Africa]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Speaker of the North West Provincial Legislature}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| honorific-prefix    = [[The Honourable]]\n| name                = Sussana Dantjie\n| native_name         = \n| native_name_lang    = \n| honorific-suffix    = [[Member of the Provincial Legislature|